<!--
  Task 2.13: Estimate PDF export template.

  Rendered by app/services/pdf_export.py's render_estimate_html(), then
  converted to PDF bytes by xhtml2pdf (substituted for the plan doc's named
  WeasyPrint — see the substitution comment in backend/pyproject.toml's
  `dependencies` list for the full rationale: WeasyPrint's GTK3/Pango/Cairo
  native runtime has no simple pip-installable path on this project's
  Windows dev machine).

  xhtml2pdf's CSS support is a practical CSS 2.1-ish subset (built on
  reportlab), not full modern CSS — no flexbox, no grid. This template
  sticks to plain block elements and <table> for the line-items grid, which
  is also simply the correct, most semantic HTML shape for tabular data
  regardless of the renderer.

  Deliberately NOT attempting a logo or custom color scheme: per the plan
  doc's "Explicitly Out of Scope for Phase 2" section, "A logo-upload / true
  visual branding system for PDF proposals... 'Branded PDF proposal' (US-4.4)
  is satisfied with a clean, consistent, company-name-labeled template — no
  `companies.logo_path` column exists in the schema doc, and adding one plus
  an upload flow is its own small feature, not required by any Phase 2 user
  story's acceptance criteria." This template is intentionally plain:
  monochrome, table-based, no images.

  All monetary/percentage strings arriving in this template's context are
  ALREADY formatted Python strings (e.g. "$1,234.56", "10.00%") — no Jinja2
  expression here does currency math or Decimal formatting itself, per this
  task's own "keeps currency formatting logic in Python, testable" rule.
-->
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<style>
  body {
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 11pt;
    color: #222222;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: 18pt;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .subtitle {
    font-size: 10pt;
    color: #555555;
    margin-top: 2px;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  table.line-items {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  table.line-items th,
  table.line-items td {
    border: 1px solid #cccccc;
    padding: 6px 8px;
    text-align: left;
  }
  table.line-items th {
    background-color: #eeeeee;
  }
  td.numeric,
  th.numeric {
    text-align: right;
  }
  table.category-breakdown {
    width: 60%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  table.category-breakdown td {
    padding: 4px 8px;
  }
  table.category-breakdown td.numeric {
    text-align: right;
  }
  table.summary {
    width: 60%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
  }
  table.summary td {
    padding: 4px 8px;
  }
  table.summary td.numeric {
    text-align: right;
  }
  table.summary tr.total td {
    border-top: 2px solid #222222;
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 13pt;
  }
  .empty-note {
    color: #777777;
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>{{ company_name }}</h1>
  <div class="subtitle">Estimate Proposal</div>

  <h2>Line Items</h2>
  {% if line_items %}
  <table class="line-items">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Category</th>
        <th>Item</th>
        <th class="numeric">Quantity</th>
        <th class="numeric">Unit Rate</th>
        <th class="numeric">Line Total</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for row in line_items %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ row.category }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.name }}</td>
        <td class="numeric">{{ row.quantity_display }}</td>
        <td class="numeric">{{ row.unit_rate_display }}</td>
        <td class="numeric">{{ row.line_total_display }}</td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <p class="empty-note">No line items have been added to this estimate yet.</p>
  {% endif %}

  <h2>Category Subtotals</h2>
  {% if category_breakdown %}
  <table class="category-breakdown">
    {% for entry in category_breakdown %}
    <tr>
      <td>{{ entry.category }}</td>
      <td class="numeric">{{ entry.subtotal_display }}</td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <p class="empty-note">No category subtotals to display.</p>
  {% endif %}

  <h2>Summary</h2>
  <table class="summary">
    <tr>
      <td>Subtotal</td>
      <td class="numeric">{{ subtotal_display }}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>{{ overhead_label }}</td>
      <td class="numeric">{{ overhead_display }}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>{{ profit_label }}</td>
      <td class="numeric">{{ profit_display }}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>{{ tax_label }}</td>
      <td class="numeric">{{ tax_display }}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr class="total">
      <td>Total</td>
      <td class="numeric">{{ total_display }}</td>
    </tr>
  </table>

</body>
</html>
